TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit GraphicData extends DocumentFormat.OpenXml.OpenXmlCompositeElement

summary.para: This class is available in Office 2007 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is a:graphicData.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)] **graphicData (Graphic Object Data)** This element specifies the reference to a graphic object within the document. This graphic object is provided entirely by the document authors who choose to persist this data within the document. [*Note*: Depending on the kind of graphical object used not every generating application that supports the OOXML framework has the ability to render the graphical object. *end note*] [*Note*: This element is not intended to reintroduce transitional schema into the strict conformance class. *end note*] |Parent Elements| |---------------------| |graphic (§20.1.2.2.16)| |Child Elements|Subclause| |--------------------|---------------| |Any element in any namespace|n/a| |Attributes|Description| |----------------|-----------------| |uri (Uniform Resource Identifier)|Specifies the , or uniform resource identifier that represents the data stored under this tag. The is used to identify the correct 'server' that can process the contents of this tag.

The possible values for this attribute are defined by the W3C XML Schema *token* datatype.| [*Note*: The W3C XML Schema definition of this element’s content model (CT_GraphicalObjectData) is located in §A.4.1. *end note*] [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlcopyrightiso.md)]
